						| The village is populated by 213 inhabitants. Today there are around hundred of houses and around 120 inhabitants living in the village.

						| In Nerezi are the neighborhoods: Chulkinska, Filskoska, Bajcheska, Nelcheska, Chavkoska. The group of houses in Chavkoska and Gjoreska are also called Koshare or Kosharci, while the rest are Pole or Poljan. The houses are rather scattered over the fields. Until 30-50 years ago, the houses were crowded because of the danger of Albanians. All in all, the village has 60 homes.